<heading>detach - Detach from current session.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>

<pre>
  detach
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Detaches the current client from the attached session
and returns control to the original session.
</paragraph>

<paragraph>
Has no effect if the client is not currently attached
to another session.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
attach, list, current, man
</paragraph>
